						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">stone standing in s. No. 155 near (the temple called) Chiṭlavvanaguḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>a.d. 778-79.</p>						

						<p>this short inscription dated in <hi rend="bold">śaka 700</hi> corresponding to a.d. 778-79 records that the figures of <hi rend="bold">śaṅkhanidhi, srīyādēvi</hi> and <hi rend="bold">padmanidhi</hi> were carved by <hi rend="bold">mukundōvaja, anumānakuśala</hi> and <hi rend="bold">būdōvaja.</hi> the three figures are sculptured in relief above the inscription.</p>						

						</summary>
